This project implements Chapter 3 of Ruby on Rails. Pay attention to me in order to get instruction.

change to project directory or all is lost!
rails new . -T
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Commit"
replace Gemfile from github.com/cs4413/sample_app

Create repository (directly or using git remote)
git remote add rogiin git@github.com:nng/sample-app1.git
git push -u origin master

bundle install
(and possibly rake db:migrate)

Start webserver in root directory of your project. 
Suggestion: create terminal view and use command "rails server", then detach view. 
URL for server: http://localhost:3000

Do git add and git commit routine.



